The network processes millions of low-cost transactions daily, attracting retail users, DeFi protocols, and onchain applications. Backed by Coinbase’s massive user base, Base continues to drive adoption through stablecoins and seamless experiences.It still has no native token, though speculation about a potential launch in 2026 grows. The team is also shifting toward a more independent architecture for better scalability and reliability. Overall, Base stays highly competitive against Arbitrum and Optimism, with strong growth momentum.

